<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Digital Accessibility_GIS Faculty Meeting (KY)</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  <style>
    *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body { font-family: 'DM Sans', Arial, sans-serif; background: #EAEEF4; min-height: 100vh; }
    .shell { max-width: 1000px; margin: 0 auto; }
    .tab-bar { display: flex; background: #003366; border-bottom: 3px solid #FFD200; position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 100; }
    .tab-btn { padding: 13px 28px; cursor: pointer; border: none; background: transparent; color: #B0C4DE; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; font-family: inherit; border-bottom: 3px solid transparent; margin-bottom: -3px; transition: all 0.15s; }
    .tab-btn.active  { color: #FFD200; background: #001f44; border-bottom-color: #FFD200; }
    .tab-btn:hover:not(.active) { color: #fff; background: #004488; }
    .tab-panel { display: none !important; }
    .tab-panel.active { display: block !important; }

:root {
  --uci-blue: #003366;
  --uci-gold: #FFD200;
  --uci-mid: #0064A4;
  --uci-light: #E8F2FA;
  --green: #1A7A4A;
  --green-light: #E6F4ED;
  --amber: #B45309;
  --amber-light: #FEF3C7;
  --text: #1a1a2e;
  --muted: #5a6070;
  --rule: #CBD5E0;
  --c1: #003366;
  --c2: #0064A4;
  --c3: #1A7A4A;
  --c4: #6B3FA0;
}

/* ===== PRINT ===== */
@media print {
  body { -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact; print-color-adjust: exact; background: white; }
  .tab-bar { display: none !important; }
  .tab-panel { display: block !important; page-break-before: auto; }
  .tab-panel + .tab-panel { page-break-before: always; }
  .page { max-width: 100%; padding: 0.4in 0.5in; box-shadow: none; margin: 0; }
  #cl-panel .page { padding-top: 0.4in; }
  a { color: var(--uci-mid) !important; }
  /* Checkboxes print as empty squares */
  #cl-panel .check-box {
    border: 2px solid #333 !important;
    background: white !important;
    width: 14px; height: 14px;
  }
  #cl-panel .check-box::after { content: "" !important; }
  #cl-panel .item-text { text-decoration: none !important; opacity: 1 !important; }
  #cl-panel .item { cursor: default; }
  /* Hide progress bar in print */
  .progress-bar-wrap, .progress-label { display: none !important; }
  /* Prevent orphaned category headers */
  #cl-panel .cat-header { page-break-after: avoid; }
  #cl-panel .cat-block { page-break-inside: avoid; }
}

body {
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif;
  background: #f4f6f9;
  color: var(--text);
  font-size: 13.5px;
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.page {
  max-width: 860px;
  margin: 30px auto;
  background: white;
  padding: 48px 52px 40px;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
}

/* HEADER */
.header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  justify-content: space-between;
  padding-bottom: 20px;
  border-bottom: 3px solid var(--uci-blue);
  margin-bottom: 28px;
  gap: 20px;
}
.header-left h1 {
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 800;
  font-size: 24px;
  color: var(--uci-blue);
  line-height: 1.2;
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}
.header-left p {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--muted);
  font-weight: 500;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
}
.deadline-badge {
  background: var(--uci-blue);
  color: white;
  padding: 10px 16px;
  text-align: center;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  min-width: 130px;
}
.deadline-badge .label {
  font-size: 12px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  font-weight: 600;
  opacity: 0.75;
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 2px;
}
.deadline-badge .date {
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 700;
  font-size: 18px;
  display: block;
  line-height: 1.2;
}
.deadline-badge .sub {
  font-size: 12px;
  opacity: 0.7;
  display: block;
  margin-top: 2px;
}

/* INTRO STRIP */
.intro-strip {
  background: var(--uci-light);
  border-left: 4px solid var(--uci-mid);
  padding: 12px 16px;
  margin-bottom: 28px;
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--uci-blue);
}
.intro-strip strong { font-weight: 600; }

/* TWO COLUMN LAYOUT */
.two-col {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 24px;
  margin-bottom: 24px;
}

/* SECTION */
.section { margin-bottom: 24px; }
.section-title {
  font-size: 12px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--uci-mid);
  margin-bottom: 12px;
  padding-bottom: 6px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
}

/* YUJA EXPLAINER */
.yuja-box {
  background: var(--uci-light);
  border: 1px solid #BDD6EC;
  padding: 16px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.yuja-box h3 {
  font-family: 'DM Sans', sans-serif; font-weight: 700;
  font-size: 16px;
  color: var(--uci-blue);
  margin-bottom: 6px;
}
.yuja-box p {
  font-size: 12.5px;
  color: var(--text);
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}
.status-row {
  display: flex;
  gap: 10px;
  margin-top: 8px;
}
.status-pill {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 6px;
  padding: 5px 10px;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 600;
  flex: 1;
  justify-content: center;
}
.status-pill.green  { background: var(--green-light); color: var(--green); border: 1px solid #A7D7BC; }
.status-pill.yellow { background: #FEF9C3; color: #92400E; border: 1px solid #FDE047; }
.status-pill.red    { background: #FEE2E2; color: #B91C1C; border: 1px solid #FCA5A5; }

/* STEP LIST */
.step-list { list-style: none; }
.step-list li {
  display: flex;
  gap: 10px;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
  align-items: flex-start;
  font-size: 12.5px;
}
.step-num {
  background: var(--uci-blue);
  color: white;
  width: 20px;
  height: 20px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 700;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  margin-top: 1px;
}
.step-list li strong { font-weight: 600; display: block; color: var(--uci-blue); }

/* CHECKLIST (handout tab) */
.checklist { list-style: none; }
.checklist li {
  display: flex;
  gap: 8px;
  margin-bottom: 8px;
  font-size: 12.5px;
  align-items: flex-start;
}
.check-icon {
  width: 16px;
  height: 16px;
  border: 2px solid var(--uci-mid);
  border-radius: 3px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  margin-top: 1px;
}
.checklist li strong { font-weight: 600; }

/* EXCEPTIONS BOX */
.exceptions-box {
  background: #FAFAFA;
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  padding: 14px 16px;
}
.exceptions-box h3 {
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--muted);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}
.exceptions-box ul { list-style: none; }
.exceptions-box ul li {
  font-size: 12px;
  padding: 3px 0;
  padding-left: 14px;
  position: relative;
  color: var(--text);
}
.exceptions-box ul li::before {
  content: "\2013";
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  color: var(--muted);
}

/* REASSURANCE BOX */
.reassurance {
  background: var(--green-light);
  border: 1px solid #A7D7BC;
  border-left: 4px solid var(--green);
  padding: 12px 16px;
  margin-bottom: 24px;
}
.reassurance p {
  font-size: 12.5px;
  color: #14532D;
}
.reassurance strong { font-weight: 600; }

/* RESOURCES TABLE */
.resource-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 10px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.resource-card {
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  padding: 12px 14px;
}
.resource-card .res-label {
  font-size: 12px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--muted);
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}
.resource-card .res-title {
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 600;
  color: var(--uci-blue);
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}
.resource-card .res-desc {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--muted);
  margin-bottom: 6px;
  line-height: 1.5;
}
.resource-card a {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--uci-mid);
  text-decoration: none;
  word-break: break-all;
  font-weight: 500;
}
.resource-card a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

/* FOOTER */
.footer {
  margin-top: 16px;
  padding-top: 12px;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--muted);
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 4px;
}

/* SKIP LINK */
.skip-link {
  position: absolute;
  top: -40px;
  left: 0;
  background: var(--uci-blue);
  color: white;
  padding: 8px 12px;
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 600;
  z-index: 100;
  text-decoration: none;
}
.skip-link:focus { top: 0; }

.note-tag {
  display: inline-block;
  background: #FEE2E2;
  color: #B91C1C;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 700;
  padding: 1px 6px;
  border-radius: 2px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  margin-right: 4px;
}

/* LAW BACKGROUND */
.law-strip {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 0;
  margin-bottom: 24px;
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
}
.law-block {
  padding: 12px 14px;
  border-right: 1px solid var(--rule);
}
.law-block:last-child { border-right: none; }
.law-block .law-label {
  font-size: 12px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--uci-mid);
  margin-bottom: 4px;
}
.law-block .law-val {
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--uci-blue);
  margin-bottom: 3px;
}
.law-block .law-desc {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--muted);
  line-height: 1.5;
}

/* HOW-TO TOOL CARDS */
.tool-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 10px;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
}
.tool-card {
  border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  padding: 12px 14px;
}
.tool-card .tool-name {
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--uci-blue);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  margin-bottom: 8px;
  padding-bottom: 6px;
  border-bottom: 2px solid var(--uci-light);
}
.tool-steps { list-style: none; }
.tool-steps li {
  font-size: 12px;
  color: var(--text);
  padding: 3px 0;
  padding-left: 16px;
  position: relative;
  line-height: 1.5;
}
.tool-steps li::before {
  content: "\2192";
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  color: var(--uci-mid);
  font-size: 12px;
  top: 4px;
}
.tool-steps li strong { color: var(--uci-blue); font-weight: 600; }

/* ======================================================
   CHECKLIST TAB — INTERACTIVE CHECKBOX STYLES
   ====================================================== */
#cl-panel .page {
  max-width: 860px;
  margin: 30px auto;
  background: white;
  padding: 48px 52px 40px;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 40px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
}

/* Category blocks */
#cl-panel .cat-block { margin-bottom: 16px; }
#cl-panel .cat-header {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 10px;
  padding: 7px 13px;
  color: white;
}
#cl-panel .cat-num {
  width: 22px; height: 22px;
  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.22);
  border-radius: 50%;
  display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  font-size: 11px; font-weight: 700;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}
#cl-panel .cat-title { font-size: 14px; font-weight: 700; flex: 1; }
#cl-panel .cat-1 .cat-header { background: var(--c1); }
#cl-panel .cat-2 .cat-header { background: var(--c2); }
#cl-panel .cat-3 .cat-header { background: var(--c3); }
#cl-panel .cat-4 .cat-header { background: var(--c4); }

/* Items */
#cl-panel .items-wrap { border: 1px solid var(--rule); border-top: none; }
#cl-panel .item {
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-start;
  gap: 11px;
  padding: 8px 13px;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background 0.12s;
  position: relative;
}
#cl-panel .item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
#cl-panel .item:nth-child(even) { background: #FAFBFC; }
#cl-panel .item:hover { background: #F0F4F8; }

/* Hidden native checkbox */
#cl-panel .check-input {
  position: absolute;
  opacity: 0;
  width: 0;
  height: 0;
  pointer-events: none;
}

/* Visual checkbox */
#cl-panel .check-box {
  width: 16px;
  height: 16px;
  border: 2px solid var(--c1);
  border-radius: 3px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  margin-top: 2px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  transition: all 0.15s;
  position: relative;
}
#cl-panel .check-box::after {
  content: "";
  font-size: 11px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: white;
  line-height: 1;
}

/* Checked state */
#cl-panel .check-input:checked + .check-box {
  border-color: var(--c1);
  background: var(--c1);
}
#cl-panel .check-input:checked + .check-box::after { content: "\2713"; }
#cl-panel .check-input:checked ~ .item-body .item-text {
  text-decoration: line-through;
  opacity: 0.5;
  transition: all 0.15s;
}

/* Focus visible for keyboard nav */
#cl-panel .check-input:focus-visible + .check-box {
  outline: 2px solid var(--uci-mid);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* Category-specific checkbox colors */
#cl-panel .cat-1 .check-box { border-color: var(--c1); }
#cl-panel .cat-2 .check-box { border-color: var(--c2); }
#cl-panel .cat-3 .check-box { border-color: var(--c3); }
#cl-panel .cat-4 .check-box { border-color: var(--c4); }
#cl-panel .cat-1 .check-input:checked + .check-box { background: var(--c1); border-color: var(--c1); }
#cl-panel .cat-2 .check-input:checked + .check-box { background: var(--c2); border-color: var(--c2); }
#cl-panel .cat-3 .check-input:checked + .check-box { background: var(--c3); border-color: var(--c3); }
#cl-panel .cat-4 .check-input:checked + .check-box { background: var(--c4); border-color: var(--c4); }

#cl-panel .cat-1 .item-note { color: var(--c1); }
#cl-panel .cat-2 .item-note { color: var(--c2); }
#cl-panel .cat-3 .item-note { color: var(--c3); }
#cl-panel .cat-4 .item-note { color: var(--c4); }

#cl-panel .item-body { flex: 1; }
#cl-panel .item-text { font-size: 12.5px; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.5; }
#cl-panel .item-text strong { font-weight: 600; }
#cl-panel .item-note { font-size: 11px; margin-top: 2px; font-style: italic; opacity: 0.85; }

/* Progress bar */
.progress-bar-wrap {
  background: #E2E8F0;
  height: 6px;
  border-radius: 3px;
  margin-bottom: 18px;
  overflow: hidden;
}
.progress-bar-fill {
  height: 100%;
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--c1), var(--c2), var(--c3));
  border-radius: 3px;
  width: 0%;
  transition: width 0.3s ease;
}
.progress-label {
  font-size: 11.5px;
  color: var(--muted);
  font-weight: 600;
  margin-bottom: 6px;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: space-between;
}


  </style>
</head>
<body>
<div class="shell">
  <div class="tab-bar" role="tablist">
    <button class="tab-btn active" id="btn-handout" role="tab" aria-selected="true" aria-controls="ho-panel" onclick="show('handout')">&#128196; &nbsp;Handout</button>
    <button class="tab-btn" id="btn-checklist" role="tab" aria-selected="false" aria-controls="cl-panel" onclick="show('checklist')">&#9989; &nbsp;Self-Check Checklist</button>
  </div>

  <!-- ============================================================
       TAB 1 — HANDOUT
       ============================================================ -->
  <div class="tab-panel active" id="ho-panel" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="btn-handout">
    <a class="skip-link" href="#main-content">Skip to main content</a>
    <div class="page">
      <main id="main-content">

      <!-- HEADER -->
      <div class="header">
        <div class="header-left">
          <h1>Digital Accessibility:<br><span style="font-size:0.82em;font-weight:700;">A Starting Point for GIS Faculty</span></h1>
          <p>UC IRVINE &middot; GIS FACULTY MEETING &middot; MARCH 11, 2026</p>
        </div>
        <div class="deadline-badge">
          <span class="label">Compliance Deadline</span>
          <span class="date">April 24,<br>2026</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- INTRO -->
      <div class="intro-strip">
        With limited exceptions, digital materials made available to students online &mdash; including Canvas content, PDFs, slides, videos, and documents &mdash; should be accessible. This is a starting point: what I've gathered from several workshops and resources. It's not complete, and it won't be perfect, but it's a baseline we can build on together!
      </div>

      <!-- LAW BACKGROUND -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title" role="heading" aria-level="2">The Legal Context</div>
        <div class="law-strip">
          <div class="law-block">
            <div class="law-label" role="heading" aria-level="3">The Federal Law</div>
            <div class="law-val">ADA Title II</div>
            <div class="law-desc">The Americans with Disabilities Act requires public universities to make all digital content accessible. A 2024 DOJ final rule clarified specific accessibility requirements for the web content and digital materials of public entities &mdash; with significant implications for online course materials, documents, and instructional content.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="law-block">
            <div class="law-label" role="heading" aria-level="3">The Standard</div>
            <div class="law-val">WCAG 2.1 Level AA</div>
            <div class="law-desc">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines &mdash; the international benchmark for accessible digital content. Covers Canvas materials: documents, slides, videos, and websites. <em>Note: WCAG 2.2 is the current version, but the DOJ and UC policy currently reference 2.1 AA as the required baseline.</em></div>
          </div>
          <div class="law-block">
            <div class="law-label" role="heading" aria-level="3">UCI's Internal Policy</div>
            <div class="law-val">UC IMT-1300</div>
            <div class="law-desc">The long-standing UC system-wide policy requiring all UC institutions to meet WCAG 2.1 AA. The 2026 DOJ deadline is now accelerating enforcement across all campuses.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- YUJA SECTION -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title" role="heading" aria-level="2">YuJa Panorama &mdash; Check What's Already in Canvas</div>
        <div class="yuja-box">
          <h3>What is YuJa Panorama?</h3>
          <p>YuJa Panorama is an accessibility platform integrated with Canvas that automatically scans your course files and flags accessibility issues. It displays <strong>color-coded indicators</strong> next to files and generates reports that help you fix problems &mdash; some right inside Canvas. It also automatically generates alternative formats for students (audio, HTML, tagged PDF), improving access without requiring additional work from you.</p>
          <div class="status-row">
            <div class="status-pill green">
              <svg aria-hidden="true" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="vertical-align:middle;flex-shrink:0;">
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="11.5" stroke="#1A7A4A" stroke-width="1.3" fill="#E6F4ED"/>
                <circle cx="12" cy="6.2" r="1.7" fill="#1A7A4A"/>
                <path d="M12 8.2 L12 14.5" stroke="#1A7A4A" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                <path d="M8.5 10.5 L12 9.5 L15.5 10.5" stroke="#1A7A4A" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <path d="M12 14.5 L9.5 18.5" stroke="#1A7A4A" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                <path d="M12 14.5 L14.5 18.5" stroke="#1A7A4A" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </svg>
              <strong>Green</strong> = Accessible. No action needed.
            </div>
            <div class="status-pill yellow">
              <svg aria-hidden="true" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="vertical-align:middle;flex-shrink:0;">
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="11.5" stroke="#92400E" stroke-width="1.3" fill="#FEF9C3"/>
                <circle cx="12" cy="6.2" r="1.7" fill="#92400E"/>
                <path d="M12 8.2 L12 14.5" stroke="#92400E" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                <path d="M8.5 10.5 L12 9.5 L15.5 10.5" stroke="#92400E" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <path d="M12 14.5 L9.5 18.5" stroke="#92400E" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                <path d="M12 14.5 L14.5 18.5" stroke="#92400E" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </svg>
              <strong>Yellow</strong> = Some issues. Fix after red items.
            </div>
            <div class="status-pill red">
              <svg aria-hidden="true" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="vertical-align:middle;flex-shrink:0;">
                <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="11.5" stroke="#B91C1C" stroke-width="1.3" fill="#FEE2E2"/>
                <circle cx="12" cy="6.2" r="1.7" fill="#B91C1C"/>
                <path d="M12 8.2 L12 14.5" stroke="#B91C1C" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                <path d="M8.5 10.5 L12 9.5 L15.5 10.5" stroke="#B91C1C" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <path d="M12 14.5 L9.5 18.5" stroke="#B91C1C" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
                <path d="M12 14.5 L14.5 18.5" stroke="#B91C1C" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              </svg>
              <strong>Red</strong> = Significant issues. Fix these first.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- TWO COLUMN -->
      <div class="two-col">

        <!-- LEFT: WORKFLOW -->
        <div class="section">
          <div class="section-title" role="heading" aria-level="2">How to Fix Issues in YuJa Panorama</div>
          <ol class="step-list">
            <li>
              <span class="step-num">1</span>
              <div><strong>Open your Canvas course</strong> Look for the colored circles next to your files. Start with the red ones.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="step-num">2</span>
              <div><strong>Click &rarr; View &rarr; Fix Issue</strong> YuJa Panorama walks you through each problem one by one, right inside Canvas.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="step-num">3</span>
              <div><strong>Fix simple issues in YuJa Panorama</strong> Alt text for images, slide titles, link text, color contrast &mdash; all fixable in-place.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="step-num">4</span>
              <div><strong>Complex issues? Contact DASH</strong> Submit a request form; they handle the harder stuff &mdash; complex PDFs, scanned documents, OCR.</div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <span class="step-num">5</span>
              <div><strong>100% green = YuJa Panorama has no further flags</strong> YuJa Panorama is your final check. Green across the board means no further flags.</div>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- RIGHT: CHECKLIST -->
        <div class="section">
          <div class="section-title" role="heading" aria-level="2">Most Common Issues to Fix</div>
          <ul class="checklist">
            <li><span class="check-icon"></span><div><strong>Images without Alt Text</strong><br>Add a brief description of what the image shows. Decorative images? Mark as &ldquo;decorative&rdquo; &mdash; screen readers will skip them.</div></li>
            <li><span class="check-icon"></span><div><strong>Missing Slide Titles</strong><br>Every slide needs a title (can be hidden) so screen readers can navigate between them.</div></li>
            <li><span class="check-icon"></span><div><strong>Vague Link Text</strong><br>&ldquo;Click here&rdquo; &rarr; use descriptive text like &ldquo;Download Week 3 Readings.&rdquo;</div></li>
            <li><span class="check-icon"></span><div><strong>PDFs without Tags</strong><br>Use Adobe Pro's &ldquo;Prepare for Accessibility&rdquo; auto-tag feature, then re-upload to Canvas.</div></li>
            <li><span class="check-icon"></span><div><strong>Videos without Captions</strong><br>Auto-captions can be a starting point, but always review for accuracy. For lecture recordings, use YuJa's caption editor to review and correct captions.</div></li>
            <li><span class="check-icon"></span><div><strong>Low Color Contrast</strong><br>YuJa Panorama flags text that's hard to read and lets you pick an accessible color right in Canvas.</div></li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- EXCEPTIONS -->
        <div class="section">
          <div class="section-title" role="heading" aria-level="2">Lower-Priority &amp; Potential Exceptions</div>
          <div class="exceptions-box">
            <h3>Potential exceptions &mdash; context-dependent, check campus guidance</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Clearly archived content kept only for reference or recordkeeping (not actively used for teaching)</li>
              <li>Files not uploaded to Canvas (shown in class only)</li>
              <li>Some unaffiliated third-party content &mdash; <em>but not content provided through a university contract or licensing arrangement</em></li>
              <li>Content published before the April 24, 2026 deadline that is no longer active</li>
              <li>Individualized, password-protected documents specific to a single person</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="font-size:12px;color:var(--amber);margin-top:8px;background:#FEF3C7;padding:7px 10px;border-radius:4px;border-left:3px solid #F59E0B;"><span class="note-tag">Important</span> Past-quarter materials still accessible to students in Canvas are considered <em>active</em>, not archived &mdash; and are in scope. If you don't want them in scope, remove them from Canvas or restrict access.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- REASSURANCE -->
        <div class="section">
          <div class="section-title" role="heading" aria-level="2">A Few Things Worth Knowing</div>
          <div class="reassurance">
            <p><strong>Accessibility vs. Accommodation:</strong> Accessibility is proactive course design for everyone; accommodations are individualized adjustments for specific students. Both matter &mdash; but they're different obligations.<br><br><strong>The expectation is not instant perfection.</strong> What matters is taking reasonable, documented steps to improve accessibility &mdash; especially for materials actively in use. Schools that faced legal action did so because they refused to act, not because they were imperfect.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div><!-- end two-col -->

      <!-- HOW-TO TOOLS -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title" role="heading" aria-level="2">Starting Fresh &mdash; Built-In Tools in Word, PowerPoint &amp; Adobe</div>
        <div class="tool-grid">

          <div class="tool-card">
            <div class="tool-name" role="heading" aria-level="3"><svg aria-hidden="true" width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 22 22" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" style="vertical-align:middle;flex-shrink:0;">
              <circle cx="11" cy="11" r="10.5" stroke="#B91C1C" stroke-width="1.2" fill="#FEE2E2"/>
              <circle cx="11" cy="6.5" r="1.8" fill="#B91C1C"/>
              <path d="M8 10h6M11 10v5.5M9 15.5l2-2 2 2" stroke="#B91C1C" stroke-width="1.4" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            </svg> YuJa Panorama &mdash; Canvas</div>
            <ul class="tool-steps">
              <li>Open your Canvas course</li>
              <li>Look for <strong>colored circles</strong> next to each file</li>
              <li>Click a red circle &rarr; <strong>View</strong></li>
              <li>Click <strong>Fix Issue</strong> on each item</li>
              <li>For images: add alt text or mark as <strong>Decorative</strong></li>
              <li>For slides: add or set a <strong>Slide Title</strong></li>
              <li>For links: replace &ldquo;click here&rdquo; with descriptive text</li>
              <li>When everything is green &rarr; <strong>done</strong></li>
            </ul>
            <p style="font-size:11.5px;color:#5a6070;margin-top:8px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Important:</strong> These categories are narrow and context-dependent. If the material is actively used for teaching or student access, treat it as in scope.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="tool-card">
            <div class="tool-name" role="heading" aria-level="3">&#128202; PowerPoint</div>
            <ul class="tool-steps">
              <li>Open your .pptx file</li>
              <li>Click <strong>Review</strong> tab in the top menu</li>
              <li>Click <strong>Check Accessibility</strong></li>
              <li>Panel opens on the right with a list of issues</li>
              <li>Click each issue &rarr; it takes you directly to the problem</li>
              <li>Right-click any image &rarr; <strong>Edit Alt Text</strong></li>
              <li>Add a slide title via <strong>View &rarr; Outline View</strong></li>
              <li>Fix <strong>Reading Order</strong>: Review &rarr; Check Accessibility &rarr; Reading Order Pane</li>
              <li>Re-upload to Canvas when done</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="tool-card">
            <div class="tool-name" role="heading" aria-level="3">&#128196; Word &amp; Adobe PDF</div>
            <ul class="tool-steps">
              <li><strong>Word:</strong> Review tab &rarr; <strong>Check Accessibility</strong></li>
              <li>Use <strong>Heading styles</strong> (H1, H2) &mdash; not just bold text</li>
              <li>Add alt text to all images (right-click &rarr; Edit Alt Text)</li>
              <li>Use descriptive hyperlink text, not bare URLs</li>
              <li>Export as PDF: <strong>Save As &rarr; PDF</strong> (preserves tags)</li>
              <li><strong>Adobe Acrobat Pro:</strong> All Tools &rarr; <strong>Prepare for Accessibility</strong></li>
              <li>Click <strong>Autotag Document</strong> &mdash; runs automatically</li>
              <li>Then add alt text to any flagged images</li>
              <li>Upload the tagged PDF to Canvas</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- UDL + DESIGN TIPS -->
      <div class="section">
        <div class="section-title" role="heading" aria-level="2">Font, Color &amp; Design &mdash; Quick Reference</div>
        <div class="law-strip">
          <div class="law-block">
            <div class="law-label" role="heading" aria-level="3">Font</div>
            <div class="law-val" style="font-size:14px;">Sans-serif, 12pt+</div>
            <div class="law-desc">Use Arial, Calibri, Aptos, or Helvetica &mdash; all standard sans-serif fonts. Avoid decorative fonts (e.g., cursive or handwriting-style). Body text minimum 12pt. Headings should be bold and clearly distinct from body text.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="law-block">
            <div class="law-label" role="heading" aria-level="3">Color &amp; Contrast</div>
            <div class="law-val" style="font-size:14px;">4.5:1 minimum ratio</div>
            <div class="law-desc">Never use color alone to convey meaning &mdash; e.g., marking a deadline only in red text. Color alone doesn't carry meaning for everyone &mdash; different ways of seeing color, grayscale printing, and low-contrast screens all affect how content reads. Always pair color with bold text or an icon (&#9888;&#65039;). YuJa Panorama and PowerPoint's checker will flag contrast issues automatically.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="law-block">
            <div class="law-label" role="heading" aria-level="3">Universal Design for Learning (UDL)</div>
            <div class="law-desc">Explore the UDL framework: <a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org" target="_blank" aria-label="CAST UDL Guidelines website">udlguidelines.cast.org</a> and UCI's own guide at <a href="https://dtei.uci.edu/resources/how-to/accessibility/" target="_blank" aria-label="UCI DTEI Inclusive Teaching page">dtei.uci.edu/resources/how-to/accessibility</a>.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

